---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SqlSandbox } from '@/lib/sql-sandbox';
---

<Layout title="Why Databases Are Special">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-8 space-y-10">
    <header class="space-y-2">
      <p class="text-xs font-mono text-muted">Chapter 01</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Why Databases Are Special</h1>
      <p class="text-muted text-lg">
        Files, caches, object stores, and databases all "store data."
        The difference is in the contract they enforce: consistency,
        access patterns, and recovery.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">1. Files Are Not Databases</h2>
      <p class="text-muted">
        Try two processes writing the same JSON file. You’ll get torn writes or last-write-wins chaos.
        Databases solve this with page-level locking, write-ahead logging, and buffer management.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">2. ACID as an Engineering Contract</h2>
      <p class="text-muted">
        Atomicity: all-or-nothing. Consistency: invariants hold at boundaries.
        Isolation: concurrent work doesn’t break invariants. Durability: committed work survives power loss.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">3. Exercise: Observe Behavior</h2>
      <p class="text-muted">Run SQL in the sandbox and observe what persists.</p>
      <div id="sandbox" class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-surface/80 p-4"></div>
    </div>

    <footer class="flex items-center justify-between pt-6 text-sm">
      <a class="text-muted hover:text-accent" href="/">← Home</a>
      <a class="text-muted hover:text-accent" href="/chapters">Chapters →</a>
    </footer>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    (function() {
      const el = document.getElementById('sandbox');
      if (!el) return;
      const sandbox = new SqlSandbox();
      sandbox.mount(el);
      window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
        window.dispatchEvent(new Event('sandbox-run-default'));
      });
    })();
  </script>
</Layout>
